ewline          4.0\sin{ ig( rac{\pi(n-106)}{59} ig)}& & {107 \leq n \leq 166}
ewline          -6.5\sin{ ig( rac{\pi(n-166)}{80} ig)}& & {167 \leq n \leq 246}
ewline          16.4\sin{ ig( rac{\pi(n-247)}{113} ig)}& & {247 \leq n \leq 365}          \end{cases}        \] Apparent solar time (\(T_{solar}\))      \[T_{solar} = T_{UTC}+ rac{E_{qt}}{60}+longitude/15\] Hour angle (\(	heta_{hr}\))      \[	heta_{hr} =  rac{T_{solar}-12}{12}\pi\] Zenith angle      \[zenith = \arccos ig({\sin{(latitude)}\sin{(	heta_d)}+\cos{(latitude)}\cos{(	heta_d)}\cos{(	heta_{hr})} ig)}\] Azimuth angle      \[        azimuth =  egin{cases}          \arcsin{()}& & {\geq 0, B \geq 0}
ewline          180-\arcsin{()}& & {B < 0}
ewline          360+\arcsin{()}& & {< 0, B \geq 0}          \end{cases}      \]      \(n - 	ext{day year}\) \(= \sin{(azimuth)} =                        - rac{\sin{(	heta_{hr})}\cos{(	heta_d)}}{\sin{(zenith)}}\) \(B = \cos{(azimuth)} =  rac{\sin{(	heta_d)}-                         \sin{(latitude)}\cos{(zenith)}}{\cos{(latitude)}\sin{(zenith)}}\)
